<h2><a name="Tour highlights"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Tour highlights</span></h2>
<p>• This fantastic 11 day tour visits Italy's most famous and beautiful lakes<br />• Staying in four star hotels with breakfast and dinner included<br />• Dedicated tour manager throughout the trip<br />• Enjoy a boat trip around Lake Garda and see Sirmione's picturesque peninsula and castle from the water<br />• Full day trips to the historic city of Verona and romantic Venice, with some free time to explore<br />• Visit the medieval city of Bergamo and travel up the cable car for amazing views<br />• Full day excursion to Lake Maggiore with a visit to the stunning Borromean Islands and their botanical gardens<br />• Explore the glamorous Lake Como and visit the gardens of Villa Carlotta<br />• Head off the beaten track with a day in sleepy Lake Orta. Explore the picturesque towns and cobbled streets<br />• Full day visit to Lake Lugano in Switzerland<br /><strong><br /></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/wonders-of-the-italian-lakes#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Itinerary"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Itinerary</span></h2>
<p><strong>Day 1: UK to Verona</strong></p>
<p><span>Fly to Verona airport where you’ll be met and transferred to your hotel in Peschiera. Take some time to settle in before heading down to meet your fellow travellers and tour manager for a welcome drink. </span></p>
<p>Meals included: Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 2: Boat tour of Lake Garda and Sirmione</strong></p>
<p><span>Spend your first full day exploring the picturesque towns and magnificent scenery of Lake Garda. One of the best ways to see Italy’s largest lake and the historic towns that line its shores is from the water. Enjoy a boat trip that will take you across the sparkling clear lagoon whilst you learn about its natural setting and historic sights. Cruise along the coast of the Sirmione peninsula and admire the luxurious villas - including that of famed opera singer Maria Callas. Watch as the thermal water bubbles from the Boiola sulphur spring and see the impressive Castle of Sirmione.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 3: Verona</strong></p>
<p><span>Just a short hop away, you’ll find one of Italy’s most striking cities, Verona. The Adige River meanders through the heart of this ancient city. Walk through winding lanes and admire bustling piazzas while an expert local guide gives you an insight to this wonderful city and its historical background.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 4: Venice</strong></p>
<p><span>Today you’ll explore the enchanting archipelago city of Venice. Traverse the city and its meandering waterways like a local on the vaporetti. Your knowledgeable local guide will take you to explore sights including the Renaissance Palazzos and Piazza San Marco with its fascinating merchant history. Marvel at the Itali-Byzanite architecture of St. Mark's Basilica with its beautifully sculpted teardrop domes that pierce the sky. See the luminous byzantine mosaics that date back to the 13th century as they glisten across the building’s façade. Later you’ll have time to see more of Venice at your own pace before heading back to your hotel.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 5: Day at leisure</strong></p>
<p><span>Take a break, sit back and relax whilst taking some time to enjoy your beautiful surroundings. Today marks the half way point on the trip where you’ll have the chance to spend the day at leisure. Choose to relax by the hotel's pool or head into Peschiera where regular ferries travel to nearby resorts on the lake.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 6: Bergamo</strong></p>
<p><span>Your journey continues towards Varese, your home for the next five nights. On the way you’ll stop in the lovely city of Bergamo. The lower part of the town, Città Bassa, is a modern metropolis that is in stark contrast to the upper part of the town, Città Alta, with its maze of medieval streets. Hop on the cable car that connects the two and take in the stunning views as you ride up. Known for its diverse architecture, here you can find impressive examples of medieval, Renaissance and Baroque styles. </span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 7: Lake Maggiore</strong></p>
<p><span>Lake Maggiore retains the feel of the ‘Golden Age’ with its stunning villas and carefully manicured botanical gardens. Start your day in Stresa where you can take in fantastic views of the lake. Your local guide with show you around the town, known for its thriving cultural scene. Afloat in the centre of the lake are three jewel-like islands, the Borromean Islands. Named after the aristocratic Borromean family who transformed the rocky islets into baroque botanical masterpieces. From the port at Stresa you’ll hop aboard a boat to set sail on the lake to explore the beautiful archipelago, stopping off to visit the 17</span><sup>th</sup><span> Century Palazzo Borromeo and its surrounding gardens.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 8: Lake Como</strong></p>
<p>Today you’ll visit another of the region's striking lakes, Lake Como. Its shoreline is surrounded by steep forested banks, dotted with beautiful ancient villages. At the southern tip of the western branch of the Y shaped lake lies the town of Como. Stroll along the waterfront promenade and visit the striking Gothic Cathedral where your local guide will give you an insight into its history and the works of art including sculptures, tapestries and paintings that the building holds. The tour will continue further north towards Tremezzo, the point where the lake branches. Here you’ll visit the elegant lakeside Villa Carlotta and its botanical gardens. The manicured terraced gardens offer up an impressive display leading right down to the lake's edge.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 9: Lake Orta</strong></p>
<p><span>Lake Orta may be slightly lesser known than its neighbouring lakes, but this plays to it’s advantage. Step off well-trodden path and spend the day getting to know this enchanting Italian lake. Watch the mountains and weather patterns reflect in the tranquil silver-blue waters and visit the medieval town of Orta San Giulio. Wander through the ancient narrow streets that are dotted with churches, shops and cafes, taking your time to take in the serene atmosphere.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 10: Lake Lugano</strong></p>
<p><span>Today ypou cross the Swiss boarder to Lugano. Here on the banks of Lake Lugano you’ll experience the merging of Swiss and Italian cultures. </span><span>You’ll see it in the architecture, hear it in the language and taste it in the local cuisine. Visit one of the picturesque border towns that line the lake. On your final evening enjoy a farewell dinner in a local restaurant.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 11: Milan - UK</strong></p>
<p><span>Transfer from your hotel to Milan Malpensa airport.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/wonders-of-the-italian-lakes#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Your holiday includes"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Your holiday includes</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>10 nights accommodation in 4* hotels</li>
<li>10 breakfasts and 10 dinners</li>
<li>Full day excursion to Verona</li>
<li>Full day excursion to Venice</li>
<li>Stop of in Bergamo with entry to the cable car</li>
<li>Full day excursion to Lake Maggiore and the Borromean Islands</li>
<li>Full day excursion to Lake Como and entry to Villa Carlotte</li>
<li>Full day excursion to Lake Orta</li>
<li>Full day excursion to Lake Lugano</li>
<li>Airport transfers</li>
</ul>
<p><span></span><strong>Your holiday excludes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Hotel city tax</li>
<li>Personal expenses and drinks</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/wonders-of-the-italian-lakes#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Hotels"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Hotels</span></h2>
<p><strong>★★★★ </strong><strong><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/italy/lake-garda/peschiera/parc-hotel">Parc Hotel,</a><span> </span>Peschiera</strong></p>
<p>The Parc Hotel is nestled in the beautiful countryside of Peschiera, a perfect location for exploring the surrounding region. The simply furnished rooms provide a comfortable space to rest your head after busy days seeing the sights. Choose from one of the indoor or outdoor pools to cool off in.</p>
<p><strong>Your Food: </strong>Dinner is a hot buffet service running from 6.30pm until 8.30pm each evening and focuses on the use of local ingredients to create a delicious and filling variety of dishes, perfect to top up your energy after a long day of activities.</p>
<p><strong>★★★★ Capolago Hotel, Varese</strong></p>
<p>Close to the shores of Lake Verese, the Capolago Hotel offers a modern retreat where you’ll be able to relax and unwind. It’s in the sleepy village of Capolago where there is just a handful of local shops and its strategic location makes it a great base for exploring the region. The spacious rooms are elegantly furnished and decorated in light fresh tones creating a tranquil environment. </p>
<p><strong>Your Food: </strong>The hotel makes sure that its guests eat well during their stay. Begin the day with a wholesome breakfast. The buffet offers a selection of sweet and savoury options including fresh seasonal fruits and home-made pastries. In the evening the restaurant serves traditional Italian cuisine made using fresh local produce. Dinner is with a three-course set menu with water and tea or coffee included. </p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/wonders-of-the-italian-lakes#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
